description: Completing this column is conditional upon whether the "ImmPort Template?" column value is set to "Yes" or "No". ImmPort supports results templates for many of the commonly used immunological assay methods. These templates facilitate the sharing and re-use of results data in a standard format. The file size name limit is 240 characters.

description: Please enter either a protocol user defined ID or ImmPort accession. One or more identifiers can be entered per subject. Separate identifiers by semicolon (;).
comment: Please enter either a protocol user defined ID or ImmPort accession.

description: A lab test panel may be linked to a single study.
comment: Please enter a study user defined ID or ImmPort accession for the study in which the lab test panel occurs. The Study ID is only required when both the lab test panel and biological sample are new.

description: The biological sample user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to a sample. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. experiment sample). The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded. Please enter either a biological sample user defined ID or ImmPort accession. A single biological sample may be linked to a lab test.

description: Please enter either a subject user defined ID or ImmPort accession for the subject from which the sample was derived. A single subject record is permitted.
comment: Please enter either a subject user defined ID or ImmPort accession for the subject from which the sample was derived.

description: The link to a study's planned visit provides temporal context for a sample's derivation from a subject.
comment: Please enter either a study's planned visit user defined ID or ImmPort accession.

description: The sample types are adopted from Uberon, Cell and CHEBI ontologies.
comment: Please choose a biological sample type from the drop down list.

description: Enter a sample type that is of finer resolution than the standard sample types provided. If the 'Biological Sample Type' is 'Other', then the sample subtype must be entered.
comment: Enter a sample type that is of finer resolution than the standard sample types provided. If the 'Biological Sample Type' is 'Other', then the sample subtype must be entered.

description: The biological sample name is not referenced by other data records.
comment: The biological sample name is an alternate identifier that is visible when the sample is shared.

description: The biological sample description is used to describe details of the sample not captured in other columns.
comment: The biological sample description is used to describe details of the sample not captured in other columns.

description: Study time collected describes the time value for when a sample was derived from a subject.
comment: Please enter a number.

description: The time units are standard terms recommended by the HIPC Standards group.
comment: Please choose from the drop down list.

description: The time zero event refers to the study milestone upon which time is based.
comment: Please choose from the drop down list.

description: Enter a time zero event if 'Other' is selected in column 'Study Time T0 Event'.
comment: Enter a time zero event if 'Other' is selected in column 'Study Time T0 Event'.

description: The lab test panel user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to lab panel. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. lab test). The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded.

description: Please enter either a protocol user defined ID or ImmPort accession. One or more identifiers can be entered per subject. Separate identifiers by semicolon (;).
comment: Please enter either a protocol user defined ID or ImmPort accession. The Protocol ID(s) is required when either the lab test panel or the biological sample are new.

description: The lab panel name describe lab test panel. Please select a lab panel name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided. This name is visible when the panel is shared.
comment: The lab panel name describes the lab test panel. Please select a lab panel name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided. This name is visible when the panel is shared.

description: This pseudo column separates meta data from results.
comment: This pseudo column separates the results (lab tests) from the lab test panel meta data. It must always appear and be the column that appears immediately after the last meta-data column and before any result columns.

description: The lab test user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer the lab test. The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The lab test identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded. This COLUMN must appear as the FIRST COLUMN for a repeating result column group.

description: The lab test name describes lab test. Please select a lab test name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided. This name is visible when the panel is shared.
comment: Please select a lab test name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided.

description: The lab test result captures the assayed value for a sample and can include letters, numbers and greater than or less than symbols.
comment: The lab test result captures the assayed value.

description: The lab test result unit describes the unit for the lab test value.
comment: The lab test result unit describes the unit for the lab test value.

description: The source ID is defined in the corresponding ImmPort template.
comment: The source ID for the assay result is either an experiment sample, a control sample, or a standard curve.

description: The source type is either an experiment sample, control sample or standard curve.
comment: Please choose from the drop down list.

description: The assay ID represents the plate or array ID where standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples were collected and assayed. This ID will be used to link standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples results.
comment: The assay ID represents the plate or array ID where standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples were collected and assayed. This ID will be used to link standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples results.

description: The assay group ID represents a collection of plates or arrays. This ID may be used to link collections of standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples results.
comment: The assay group ID represents a collection of plates or arrays. This ID may be used to link collections of standard curves, control samples, and experiment samples results.

description: The analyte describes what is being measured in an assay. The list of values displays common immunology gene symbol and gene symbol terms on the left and their preferred term on the right, each component separated by a semi-colon. Please select a name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided. This name is visible when the result is shared.
comment: The analyte is the target (e.g protein, DNA, RNA) that is being assayed by the reagent. The list of values displays common immunology gene symbol and gene symbol terms on the left and their preferred term on the right, each component separated by a semi-colon. Please select a name from the list provided if the name matches your name or enter a name if there is not an appropriate one provided. This name is visible when the result is shared.

description: Mean Fluorescence Intensity
comment: Mean Fluorescence Intensity

description: The reported concentration value of the standard curve sample or calculated from the MFI using the standard curve.
comment: A number is expected.

description: The concentration unit of the standard curve sample or calculated from the MFI using the standard curve
comment: The concentration unit of the standard curve sample or calculated from the MFI using the standard curve.

description: The position on the assay plate.
comment: The position on the assay plate.

description: Additional descriptive information.
comment: Additional descriptive information.

description: The experiment sample identifier must be stored in ImmPort or in the experimentsamples.txt template.
comment: Please enter either an experiment sample user defined ID or ImmPort accession.

description: The NCBI Gene symbol for the gene being assayed. Please select a gene symbol from the list provided if the gene symbol matches your symbol or enter a symbol if there is not an appropriate one provided. This symbol is visible when the result is shared. If the gene symbol is a NCBI Gene Symbol that is provided in the list, then the columns 'Gene Name' and 'Gene ID' will also be overwritten by the gene name and Entrez Gene ID provided by NCBI.
comment: The NCBI Gene symbol for the gene being assayed. Please select a gene symbol from the list provided if the gene symbol matches your symbol or enter a symbol if there is not an appropriate one provided. This symbol is visible when the result is shared.

description: This value could be absolute or relative. For example, an absolute expression value could be 6 ng RNA/mg intestine. In this case, 6 should be entered in the 'Expression value of target RNA' column, while ng RNA/ mg intestine is in the 'Expression unit of target RNA' column. A relative expression value, like signal versus GAPDH, could be 2.07. In this case, 2.07 should be in the 'Expression value of target RNA' column, while relative to GAPDH is in the 'Expression unit of target RNA' column.
comment: A number is expected.

description: The unit for the Expression Value Of Target Nucleic ACID. Please select a unit from the list provided if the unit matches your unit or enter a unit if there is not an appropriate one provided.
comment: The unit for the Expression Value Of Target Nucleic ACID. Please select a unit from the list provided if the unit matches your unit or enter a unit if there is not an appropriate one provided.

description: The NCBI Gene ID for the gene being assayed. A number is expected.
comment: A number is expected.

description: The NCBI Gene name for the gene being assayed.
comment: The NCBI Gene name for the gene being assayed.

description: Additional identifier(s) for the gene being assayed.
comment: Additional identifier(s) for the gene being assayed.

description: Comments captures additional descriptive information.
comment: Comments captures additional descriptive information.

description: The protocol user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to a protocol document. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. study). The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded.

description: The protocol file name in this column must be an exact spelling match to a file in the ZIP archive that is uploaded. This includes the file extensions which may be hidden depending upon your computer's settings. The file size name limit is 240 characters.
comment: The protocol file name is the document uploaded and linked to the protocol ID. The file name must be an exact spelling match including the file extension. The file size name limit is 240 characters.

description: The protocol name is not referenced by other data records.
comment: The protocol name is an alternate identifier that is visible when the protocol is shared.

description: The summary is a brief description of the protocol's content.
comment: The protocol summary describes the purpose of the protocol.

description: The protocol type uses a preferred list of terms to characterize the protocol's content.
comment: The protocol type is chosen from a list of preferred terms.

description: The experiment sample user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to this sample. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. assay results). The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded.

description: ImmPort expects array gene expression results to be deposited in NCBI GEO since this is a prerequisite for publication. Please choose this repository name from the list.
comment: Array gene expression results are expected to be deposited in NCBI GEO Please choose this repository name from the list.

description: The public repository accession should be the most granular or highest resolution provided (e.g. sample level accession, not sample group accession).
comment: Enter the accession that links to the assay result file(s).

description: The reagent user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to an assay reagent. The nature of the assay reagent is assay specific and may be an array, an antibody or a typing kit. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. experiment sample). The user defined ID is not shared.
comment: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded.

description: The individual reagents are defined in assay specific reagent templates (e.g. flow cytometry, ELISA). The data provider may define a set or panel of reagents used in a single assay (e.g a panel of fluorochrome conjugated monoclonal antibodies).
comment: Provide a list of individual reagents that comprise the reagent set. Separate the individual reagent IDs with a semi-colon.

description: The assay reagent description provides further details on the nature and purpose of the reagent.
comment: A supplemental description of the assay reagent that expands on its Name and User Defined ID.

description: The reagent name is not referenced by other data records.
comment: The reagent name is an alternate ID that is shared.

description: The reagent set type indicates the assay type with which the reagent set is used.
comment: Choose from a list of preferred assay types.

description: The reagent user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to an assay reagent. description: The reagent name is not referenced by other data records.
comment: The reagent name is an alternate ID that is shared.

description: The assay reagent description provides further details on the nature and purpose of the reagent.
comment: A supplemental description of the assay reagent that expands on its Name and User Defined ID.

description: The source of a reagent may be important for evaluating assay results.
comment: The manufacturer is the source of a reagent and may include commercial vendors as well as non-commercial sources (e.g. collaborating labs).

description: The reagent's catalog ID provides a reference to the reagent source and description.
comment: If the assay reagent is a commercial product, enter the vendor's catalog identifier. If the reagent is a custom preparation enter 'NA'.

description: The lot number is helpful to understand possible batch specific differences in assay results.
comment: The lot number is often provided by a reagent source when the reagent is replenished over time.

description: The web link is often the vendor's web site.
comment: An internet address that may provide details of an assay reagent.

description: If the reagent is from a non-commercial source, the contact information should indicate with whom to communicate to get further details.
